no-new.description:
Description

This rule is aimed at maintaining consistency and convention by disallowing constructor calls using thenewkeyword that do not assign the resulting object to a variable.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-new: "error"*/

new Thing();

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-new: "error"*/

const thing = new Thing();

Foo();
